41 such employer less than the minimum wage required to be paid by employers to
42 employees under federal law; provided, however, that:
43 (A) During the period of July 1, 2026, through June 30, 2027, such employer shall pay
44 individuals with disabilities at least half of the minimum wage required to be paid by
45 employers to employees under federal law; and
46 (B) On and after July 1, 2027, such employer shall no longer utilize such certificate to
47 pay individuals with disabilities less than the minimum wage required to be paid by
48 employers to employees under federal law."
49 SECTION 4.
50 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025.
51 SECTION 5.
52 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
